ce%5C%22%3Ewomen%E2%80%99s%20organisations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2Faidwa-strongly-opposes-ucc-letter-law-commission%5C%22%3Eand%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeoplesdemocracy.in%2F2023%2F0716_pd%2Faidwa-memorandum-law-commission-uniform-civil-code%5C%22%3Ehave%20opposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC).%20They%20have%20emphasised%20that%20merely%20having%20uniform%20laws%20will%20not%20guarantee%20women%20equal%20rights%20or%20eradicate%20the%20discrimination%20inherent%20in%20various%20patriarchal%20and%20discriminatory%20personal%20laws.%20They%20argue%20that%20uniformity%20alone%20does%20not%20ensure%20equality%20and%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20either%20progressive%20legislation%20or%20justice%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20highlighted%20the%20disappointing%20history%20of%20reform%20initiated%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20government.%20They%20said%20it%20had%20never%20prioritised%20gender%20justice.%20Despite%20numerous%20demands%2C%20such%20as%20reforming%20inequitable%20aspects%20of%20Hindu%20Personal%20Laws%2C%20the%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20also%20expressed%20concerns%20that%20a%20UCC%20under%20the%20current%20regime%20may%20merely%20replicate%20existing%20Hindu%20Laws%2C%20rather%20than%20advancing%20gender%20justice.%20They%20argue%20that%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20UCC%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%20seems%20to%20target%20Muslims%20and%20Muslim%20Personal%20Laws%2C%20which%20the%20government%20has%20consistently%20criticised%20since%20coming%20into%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20proposed%20Uttarakhand%20UCC%20intentionally%20excludes%20the%20Adivasi%20community%2C%20who%20constitute%203%25%20of%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20demonstrates%20insensitivity%20towards%20both%20the%20progressive%20elements%20of%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law%20and%20the%20discriminatory%20aspects%20of%20Hindu%20Personal%20Law.%20Certain%20provisions%20added%20to%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20are%20regressive%2C%20discriminatory%2C%20and%20unconstitutional.%20Additionally%2C%20while%20ostensibly%20acknowledging%20live-in-relationships%20between%20consenting%20heterosexual%20adults%2C%20the%20Bill%20violates%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20partner.%20It%20imposes%20impractical%20conditions%20on%20these%20relationships%20by%20mandating%20registration%20and%20subjecting%20them%20to%20open%20%E2%80%9Cscrutiny%E2%80%9D%2C%20under%20vague%20standards%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20policy%20and%20morality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetrogressive%20provisions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20provisions%20of%20the%20UCC%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20duplication%20of%20those%20in%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%20(HMA)%20of%201955%20and%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20(SMA)%2C%20with%20some%20exceptions.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20conditions%20for%20entering%20into%20a%20marriage%20closely%20resemble%20those%20outlined%20in%20the%20HMA%20and%20SMA.%20However%2C%20a%20retrogressive%20provision%20says%20that%20parties%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20marry%20within%20certain%20prohibited%20relationships%20unless%20the%20custom%20or%20usage%20of%20one%20of%20them%20permits%20such%20a%20marriage.%20It%20further%20says%20that%20these%20customs%20and%20usage%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20order%20and%20morality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20leaves%20the%20field%20open%20for%20the%20courts%20to%20interpret%20public%20policy%20and%20morality%20according%20to%20their%20way%20of%20thinking%20and%20ideology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grounds%20for%20judicial%20separation%20and%20divorce%20are%20the%20same%20as%20those%20in%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20and%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20except%20that%20the%20divorce%20provisions%20have%20been%20widened%20to%20lay%20down%20another%20retrogressive%20additional%20ground%20which%20says%20that%20if%20either%20spouse%20converts%20to%20another%20religion%2C%20the%20other%20spouse%20can%20ask%20for%20a%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20the%20anti-human%20rights%20provision%20that%20allows%20for%20a%20claim%20for%20restitution%20of%20conjugal%20rights%20has%20also%20been%20retained%20in%20this%20Code.%20This%20right%20is%20an%20outdated%20and%20unconstitutional%20provision%20of%20English%20Law%2C%20which%20allows%20one%20party%20to%20the%20marriage%20to%20ask%20the%20court%20to%20restore%20his%20or%20her%20conjugal%20rights%20to%20the%20other%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sections%20on%20interim%20maintenance%20and%20permanent%20alimony%20have%20also%20been%20mechanically%20replicated.%20If%20there%20had%20been%20any%20intentions%20to%20advance%20or%20improve%20the%20lives%20of%20separated%20and%20deserted%20women%2C%20who%20are%20forced%20into%20lengthy%20legal%20battles%2C%20at%20least%20the%20widely%20accepted%20criteria%20for%20awarding%20maintenance%20could%20have%20been%20written%20into%20the%20law.%20Indian%20courts%20have%20laid%20down%20that%20the%20maintenance%2C%20which%20should%20be%20awarded%20by%20the%20court%2C%20should%20be%20commensurate%20with%20the%20standards%20of%20living%20of%20the%20parties.%20The%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%20also%20lays%20down%20that%20the%20amount%20granted%20to%20a%20woman%20as%20monetary%20relief%20should%20be%20adequate%2C%20fair%2C%20reasonable%20and%20consistent%20with%20the%20standard%20of%20living%20to%20which%20the%20aggrieved%20person%20is%20accustomed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20has%20not%20been%20done.%20Women%20have%20to%20fight%20a%20long%2C%20weary%20battle%20in%20the%20courts%20to%20receive%20an%20extremely%20inadequate%20sum%20as%20maintenance.%20While%20the%20section%20on%20interim%20maintenance%20says%20that%20this%20should%20be%20decided%20within%20two%20months%20of%20the%20filing%20of%20the%20application%2C%20this%20seldom%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdded%20to%20this%20is%20the%20burden%20of%20proving%20the%20income%20of%20the%20husband%2C%20which%20is%20impossible%20for%20most%20wives.%20Some%20courts%20deny%20maintenance%20to%20a%20woman%20if%20she%20leaves%20the%20home%20or%20is%20seen%20at%20fault.%20The%20law%20should%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20maintenance%20is%20not%20a%20largesse%20granted%20by%20the%20court%2C%20but%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rights%20that%20a%20woman%20has%20acquired%20by%20contributing%20to%20the%20household.%20However%2C%20none%20of%20these%20issues%20have%20been%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20sections%20for%20permanent%20alimony%20should%20have%20been%20reframed%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20women%20to%20actually%20get%20the%20alimony.%20The%20fact%20that%20none%20of%20these%20issues%20were%20tackled%2C%20shows%20that%20the%20intention%20of%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20code%20was%20not%20to%20bring%20greater%20gender%20justice%20but%20to%20force%20a%20majoritarian%20UCC%20on%20all%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%2035%20on%20custody%20of%20children%20is%20the%20same%20as%20that%20in%20the%20HMA%20and%20SMA.%20However%2C%20a%20sub-section%202%20has%20been%20added%2C%20in%20which%20the%20court%20has%20been%20enjoined%20to%20keep%20the%20best%20interest%20and%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20child%20as%20a%20paramount%20consideration.%20A%20condition%20has%20also%20been%20added%20to%20sub-section%202%20that%20the%20custody%20of%20the%20minor%20child%20of%20less%20than%20five%20years%20shall%20ordinarily%20be%20with%20the%20mother.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20though%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20code%20could%20have%20made%20both%20the%20mother%20and%20father%20equal%20guardians%20of%20the%20child%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20so%20despite%20this%20being%20a%20demand%20for%20a%20long%20time%20by%20various%20women%E2%80%99s%20groups%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwhat-a-gender-just-uniform-civil-code-could-look-like%5C%22%3EWhat%20a%20Gender-Just%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Could%20Look%20Like%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20retrogressive%20section%20in%20the%20UCC%20talks%20of%20disposal%20of%20the%20estate%20of%20either%20party%20and%20states%20that%20the%20court%20may%20decide%20to%20make%20such%20provisions%20for%20the%20estate%20as%20it%20deems%20just%20and%20proper%20in%20favour%20of%20either%20party.%20For%20some%20time%20now%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20and%20groups%20have%20been%20demanding%20equal%20rights%20to%20marital%20property%20for%20women.%20Marital%20property%20refers%20to%20assets%20acquired%20either%20jointly%20or%20individually%20by%20the%20parties%20during%20the%20course%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20law%2C%20as%20it%20stands%20now%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20recognise%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20the%20property%20bought%20by%20the%20parties%20and%20gives%20it%20to%20the%20person%20in%20whose%20name%20the%20property%20has%20been%20bought.%20This%20often%20means%20that%20women%20and%20children%20are%20left%20without%20any%20assets%20of%20the%20household%20when%20a%20breakdown%20of%20a%20marriage%20occurs%2C%20since%20women%20are%20seldom%20the%20named%20owners.%20A%20recent%20Madras%20high%20court%20judgment%20recognised%20the%20productive%20and%20equal%20value%20of%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20household%20work%20and%20held%20that%20she%20was%20entitled%20to%20an%20equal%20share%20of%20the%20assets%20on%20separation.%20However%2C%20the%20UCC%2C%20instead%20of%20recognising%20women%E2%80%99s%20marital%20property%20rights%2C%20has%20made%20a%20neutral%20provision%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20advance%20gender%20justice%20and%20can%20be%20misused%20by%20unscrupulous%20spouses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20attack%20on%20Muslims%20is%20evident%20through%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20UCC.%20While%20there%20has%20been%20a%20demand%20from%20within%20the%20Muslim%20community%20to%20outlaw%20Halala%2C%20the%20Code%20takes%20a%20further%20step%20by%20criminalising%20it.%20This%20mirrors%20the%20approach%20of%20the%20Triple%20Talaq%20legislation%20(The%20Muslim%20Women%20Protection%20of%20Rights%20on%20Marriage%20Act%2C%202019)%2C%20which%20punishes%20a%20Muslim%20male%20for%20pronouncing%20instant%20Triple%20Talaq%20with%20imprisonment.%20Thus%2C%20while%20no%20man%20from%20any%20other%20community%20faces%20punishment%20for%20unjustly%20leaving%20or%20deserting%20his%20wife%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20has%20made%20a%20Muslim%20man%20guilty%20of%20a%20criminal%20offence%20punishable%20by%20imprisonment%20merely%20for%20leaving%20his%20wife%20by%20pronouncing%20triple%20talaq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20present%20Act%2C%20if%20a%20person%20compels%2C%20abets%2C%20or%20induces%20(terms%20that%20are%20somewhat%20vague%20and%20can%20be%20broadly%20interpreted)%20another%20person%20to%20practice%20%3Cem%3ENikah%20Halala%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20they%20can%20be%20sentenced%20to%20up%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20and%20fined%20Rs%201%20lakh.%20Furthermore%2C%20a%20marriage%20cannot%20be%20dissolved%20under%20the%20Code%20except%20in%20accordance%20with%20its%20provisions%2C%20and%20a%20draconian%20provision%20has%20unreasonably%20and%20unjustly%20made%20a%20violation%20of%20this%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%20three%20years%E2%80%99%20imprisonment%20and%20a%20fine.%20Presumably%2C%20this%20section%20has%20been%20framed%20to%20prevent%20extrajudicial%20divorces%20in%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20unilateral%20right%20of%20divorce%20that%20is%20available%20to%20the%20Muslim%20man%2C%20divorce%20in%20Muslim%20law%20can%20also%20be%20done%20through%20mutual%20consent.%20The%20wife%20under%20Muslim%20law%20also%20has%2C%20unlike%20any%20woman%20in%20any%20other%20law%2C%20a%20right%20to%20ask%20for%20%3Ci%3EKhula%3C%2Fi%3E%20(divorce)%20and%20to%20be%20granted%20it.%20This%20has%20been%20pronounced%20to%20be%20an%20inalienable%20right%20of%20Muslim%20women%20to%20ask%20for%20unilateral%20separation.%20Thus%2C%20parts%20of%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law%2C%20which%20benefitted%20Muslim%20women%2C%20have%20also%20been%20done%20away%20with%2C%20which%20requires%20all%20persons%20to%20go%20through%20a%20lengthy%20prolonged%20litigation%20for%20divorce%20only%20on%20the%20grounds%20based%20on%20the%20fault%20of%20the%20other%20spouse%20stipulated%20in%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%20and%20Special%20Marriage%20Act.%20For%20no%20good%20reasons%2C%20the%20practice%20of%20%3Cem%3Eiddat%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20also%20been%20discontinued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmuslims-and-the-ucc-the-fear-of-majoritarianism-is-real-and-cant-be-brushed-aside%5C%22%3EMuslims%20and%20the%20UCC%3A%20The%20Fear%20of%20Majoritarianism%20Is%20Real%20and%20Can%E2%80%99t%20Be%20Brushed%20Aside%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20relating%20to%20succession%20in%20the%20code%20are%20also%20those%20which%20are%20applicable%20to%20Hindus%20under%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20and%20the%20Indian%20Succession%20Act%20which%20talks%20of%20the%20general%20laws%20relating%20to%20Wills%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20succession%20to%20the%20estates%20of%20Christians%20and%20Parsis.%20However%2C%20some%20beneficial%20provisions%20of%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law%20which%20restrict%20the%20right%20to%20Will%20to%20only%20one-third%20of%20the%20property%20away%20from%20heirs%20have%20not%20been%20recognised.%20The%20right%20to%20Will%20all%20one%E2%80%99s%20property%20has%20been%20taken%20from%20English%20Law.%20However%2C%20some%20European%20and%20others%20countries%20have%20put%20restrictions%20on%20the%20right%20to%20Will%20to%20safeguard%20heirs.%20Women%20in%20India%20have%20been%20demanding%20this%20right%20so%20that%20the%20property%20is%20not%20willed%20away%20from%20them%20and%20daughters%20are%20not%20disinherited%20through%20Wills.%20This%20also%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20Code%20is%20not%20trying%20to%20either%20reform%20the%20law%20or%20make%20it%20gender%20just.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20regarding%20succession%20in%20the%20Code%20are%20also%20applicable%20to%20Hindus%20under%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20and%20the%20Indian%20Succession%20Act%2C%20which%20addresses%20general%20laws%20relating%20to%20%E2%80%98wills%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20succession%20to%20the%20estates%20of%20Christians%20and%20Parsis.%20However%2C%20some%20beneficial%20provisions%20of%20Muslim%20Personal%20Law%2C%20which%20restrict%20the%20right%20to%20will%20to%20only%20one-third%20of%20the%20property%20away%20from%20heirs%2C%20have%20not%20been%20recognised.%20The%20right%20to%20will%20all%20one%E2%80%99s%20property%20has%20been%20adopted%20from%20English%20Law.%20Nevertheless%2C%20some%20European%20and%20other%20countries%20have%20imposed%20restrictions%20on%20the%20right%20to%20will%20to%20safeguard%20heirs.%20Women%20in%20India%20have%20been%20advocating%20for%20this%20right%20to%20prevent%20the%20property%20from%20being%20willed%20away%20from%20them%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20daughters%20are%20not%20disinherited%20through%20wills.%20This%20also%20underscores%20that%20the%20Code%20is%20not%20attempting%20to%20reform%20the%20law%20or%20make%20it%20gender-just.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20area%2C%20however%2C%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20proposed%20Code%20have%20been%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20section%2015%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20(HSA)%2C%20if%20a%20female%20Hindu%20dies%20intestate%2C%20her%20self-acquired%20property%20unfairly%20devolves%20on%20the%20heirs%20of%20the%20husband%2C%20and%20only%20then%20upon%20her%20own%20mother%20and%20father%20if%20she%20has%20no%20children%20or%20a%20husband.%20A%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Flawschoolcolumn%2Fhindu-succession-act-for-female-intestates-221707%5C%22%3Ejudgment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20upholding%20the%20statutory%20law%2C%20commented%20on%20the%20discrimination%20against%20the%20woman%E2%80%99s%20own%20parents%2C%20who%20could%20inherit%20only%20if%20her%20father%20and%20mother-in-law%20were%20not%20alive.%20In%20one%20instance%2C%20a%20working%20woman%2C%20a%20childless%20widow%20who%20lived%20with%20her%20parents%2C%20died%2C%20and%20her%20property%20was%20given%20to%20her%20in-laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%2015%20of%20the%20HSA%20also%20unfairly%20stipulates%20that%20any%20property%20inherited%20by%20a%20woman%20from%20her%20father%20or%20mother%20will%20devolve%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20her%20sons%20or%20daughters%20or%20their%20children%2C%20upon%20the%20heirs%20of%20the%20father.%20Similarly%2C%20any%20property%20inherited%20by%20a%20woman%20from%20her%20husband%20or%20her%20in-laws%20would%20devolve%20upon%20the%20heirs%20of%20the%20husband%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20her%20children%20and%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20UCC%20aims%20to%20eliminate%20the%20different%20rules%20of%20succession%20for%20the%20estate%20of%20male%20and%20female%20heirs%2C%20making%20the%20law%20more%20equitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20far%20as%20agricultural%20land%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20UP%20Zamindari%20Abolition%20and%20Land%20Reforms%20Act%2C%201950%2C%20which%20extends%20to%20Uttarakhand%2C%20still%20unfairly%20states%20that%20the%20heirs%20of%20a%20Bhumidar%20or%20Asami%20in%20the%20first%20place%20will%20only%20include%20the%20widow%2C%20an%20unmarried%20daughter%20and%20male%20lineal%20descendants.%20A%20married%20daughter%20can%20only%20inherit%20if%20they%20and%20the%20Bhumidar%E2%80%99s%20parents%20are%20not%20alive.%20Though%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%20was%C2%A0%20amended%20in%202005%20to%20withdraw%20the%20exemption%20earlier%20given%20to%20the%20Land%20Reforms%20Act%20from%20the%20application%20of%20the%20HSA%2C%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government%20has%20not%20seen%20it%20fit%20to%20remove%20this%20discriminatory%20provision%20in%20its%20Land%20Reforms%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20procedure%20prescribed%20under%20section%20381%20of%20the%20proposed%20Bill%20mandates%20the%20compulsory%20registration%20of%20live-in%20relationships%20with%20the%20registrar.%20The%20registrar%20in%20the%20Code%20is%20vested%20with%20very%20wide%20powers%20to%20summon%20the%20parties%20for%20verification%20and%20ask%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnecessary%E2%80%9D%20additional%20information%20and%20evidence.%20One%20can%20only%20imagine%20the%20misuse%20that%20this%20verification%20process%20can%20result%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provision%20is%20obviously%20unconstitutional%20and%20directly%20interferes%20with%20the%20rights%20of%20adult%20human%20beings%20to%20choose%20their%20partners%20and%20live%20with%20whomever%20they%20want%20without%20any%20scrutiny%20from%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20a%20draconian%20proviso%20to%20this%20section%20stipulates%20that%20registration%20can%20be%20denied%20if%20the%20live-in%20relationship%20is%20against%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20policy%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmorality.%E2%80%9D%20Thus%20the%20registrar%20can%2C%20by%20moral%20policing%2C%20refuse%20to%20register%20a%20live-in-relationship%20if%20it%20is%20against%20patriarchal%20norms%20which%20he%20espouses%20and%20bring%20a%20halt%20to%20inter-caste%20and%20inter-faith%20and%20other%20relationships.%20Furthermore%2C%20it%20will%20be%20obligatory%20for%20the%20partners%20of%20the%20live-in%20relationship%20within%20the%20state%20and%20absurdly%20outside%20the%20state%20(if%20one%20of%20them%20is%20an%20Uttarakhandi)%20to%20register.%20The%20non-registration%20within%20the%20month%20of%20the%20relationship%20will%20result%20in%20a%20punishable%20offence%20for%20a%20term%20of%20imprisonment%2C%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20provisions%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20a%20live-in%20relationship%20to%20exist.%20The%20act%20of%20registration%20of%20a%20live-in-relationship%20is%2C%20thus%2C%20not%20an%20act%20which%20recognises%20live-in-relationships%20but%20an%20act%20which%20seeks%20to%20regulate%20how%20and%20with%20whom%20these%20relationships%20can%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20proposed%20Uttarakhand%20UCC%20does%20not%20promote%20either%20gender%20justice%20or%20substantive%20equality%20for%20women%20or%20further%20the%20cause%20for%20a%20just%20and%20equal%20family%20code%20for%20all%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2021st%20Law%20Commission%20had%20said%20that%20the%20UCC%20was%20neither%20necessary%20nor%20desirable%20and%20the%20personal%20laws%20of%20each%20community%20could%20easily%20be%20reformed%20separately%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20affected%20members%20of%20that%20community.%20It%20has%20further%20remarked%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20countries%20are%20now%20moving%20towards%20recognition%20of%20difference%2C%20and%20the%20mere%20existence%20of%20difference%20does%20not%20imply%20discrimination%2C%20but%20is%20indicative%20of%20robust%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKirti%20Singh%20is%20a%20lawyer%20and%20an%20activist.%20She%20is%20a%20former%20member%20(part-time)%20of%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20and%20a%20legal%20advisor%20in%20AIDWA.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707820236000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13111222%2Fimage-1824.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-uniform-civil-code-falls-short-in-advancing-gender-justice%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Critics%20argue%20that%20while%20the%20UCC%20aims%20to%20standardise%20laws%20across%20different%20communities%2C%20it%20fails%20to%20address%20key%20issues%20such%20as%20women's%20rights%20to%20marital%20property%2C%20live-in%20relationships%2C%20and%20inheritance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-the-uniform-civil-code-falls-short-in-advancing-gender-justice%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mobile%20internet%20suspended%20in%20Senegal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707820093000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107660325%2Cimgsize-91920.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmobile-internet-suspended-in-senegal%2Farticleshow%2F107659643.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107659643.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%20Mobile%20internet%20access%20in%20Senegal%20was%20suspended%20on%20Tuesday%20for%20the%20second%20time%20this%20month%2C%20the%20communications%20ministry%20said%2C%20after%20authorities%20banned%20a%20march%20against%20the%20delay%20to%20February's%20presidential%20election.%20President%20Macky%20Sall's%20decision%20to%20push%20back%20the%20February%2025%20vote%20until%20December%20plunged%20Senegal%20into%20a%20crisis%20which%20has%20seen%20three%20dead%20amid%20clashes%20between%20protesters%20and%20security%20forces.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmobile-internet-suspended-in-senegal%2Farticleshow%2F107659643.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmobile-internet-suspended-in-senegal%2Famp_articleshow%2F107659643.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmob