m%20count%20resulted%20in%20the%20secondary%20end%20product%20being%20the%20earthworm%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20study%20included%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F332396%2Fhow-to-make-bio-enzymes-from-kitchen-waste-at-home-diy-steps-by-kolkata-gardener-nita-singh%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evegetable%20waste%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20aquatic%20weed%20(water%20hyacinth)%20as%20prime%20substrates%2C%20both%20in%20mono-substrate%20composting%20and%20co-composting.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20entire%20study%2C%20we%20have%20converted%2015%20tonnes%20of%20waste%20collected%20from%20the%20markets%20and%20ponds%20around%20the%20IIT%20Guwahati%20campus%20(350%20kg%20per%20day).%20The%20confidence%20that%20we%20gained%20through%20the%20study%20is%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20we%20are%20suggesting%20that%20the%20technology%20can%20handle%20sizable%20quantities.%20We%20believe%20this%20process%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20reshape%20organic%20waste%20treatment%20facilities%20globally%2C%20providing%20an%20environmentally%20compatible%20solution%20to%20mitigate%20contamination%20hazards%20and%20produce%20an%20outstanding%20soil%20conditioner%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20IIT-Guwahati)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707746351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341515%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr%20Ajay%20S%20Kalamdhad%20led%20a%20group%20of%20IIT-Guwahati%20researchers%20to%20innovate%20a%20two-stage%20fast%20biodegradation%20technique%20that%20can%20aid%20municipal%20corporations%20in%20eco-friendly%20organic%20waste%20management.%20It%20also%20produces%20%E2%80%98Mati%20Dhan%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20a%20top-notch%20ve